metadata.name: Generative Fantasies: 101 Compositions #18
metadata.description:
This could be a follow-up to Herbert W. Franke's finding of interesting connections between Constructivism and Generative art, where at first, technological limits allowed only simple line drawings, based on fixed proportions, and later were extended by the use of random generators. Constructivism, as an art movement, sought to depict modern civilization, the symbiotic relationship between technology and art, industrialization, and urban spaces. Iakov Chernikhov (Яков Чернихов), an architect and graphic artist, was one of the influential figures in Constructivism. He extensively used the two-point perspective with an observation point below the ground in his drawings. 

In this (my) exploration of two-point perspective, random, colorful, and glassy constructions visual resemblance to Chernikhov’s oeuvre is inescapable. Therefore the title is a play on the original title of his book Architectural Fantasies: 101 Compositions in Color, 101 Architectural Miniatures from 1933.

The subtle grain effect is done with p5.grain library by Gorilla Sun (@gorillasu) & meezwhite (@meezwhite). 

Look out for the FOMO keyboard key to unlock more variations.

metadata.name: tratti #299
metadata.description:
"tratti" is an Italian word that has many different meanings. When we started working on this piece, we wanted to create something that combines our traits ("tratti" in Italian).
We had this urge to channel the turbulent times we're living in now into this artwork using just lines ("tratti" in Italian).

We don't know what to do now, we're here, and that's all that matters. We're here for our families, our friends, and our community. Like everything in life, there are joyful times and challenging times. We must accept happiness as something that is not constant but that we feel at times (a "tratti" in Italian).

With "tratti", we want to send a message to every disheartened human being: "Stay strong and never let anyone or anything crush the hope in you. Joyful times are around the corner".

---- 

© 2022 — Alessandro Fiore x Emanuele Pasin

metadata.name: Release #20
metadata.description:
[…]

More than anything she had wanted to show him where she had lived, where, at a specific time every year, endless fields sent a new cycle of pods on their way.

She preferred to experience these moments alone, imagining the spectacle was being performed just for her. The whole act carried a promise of new beginnings, of paths yet to be taken.

She wasn't really part of any of this, but she too had the coordinates to her own life programmed into her genes.

Any decision would be true now, any path free.

A chorus of explosions sounded as the field burst open.

[…]

–

You can append these parameters to the URL:

[scale=<number>] scale the renderer.
[long-side=<number>] define the number of pixels of the longest side.
[animation=false] skip animating the lines.
[mode=monotone] activate monotone mode.
[detail=<number 0–1>] coarser (0) or finer (1) lines, default: 0.5.

Press [control / command + s] or [tap and hold] to save the current frame.
	- in normal mode: PNG file.
	- in monotone mode: SVG file, suitable for plotting.

Note: The monotone SVG file has no defined dimensions. It is suitable for plotting at 30 × 30 cm. with a 0.25 mm. pen tip. When plotting in larger sizes, you can increase the [detail] parameter to keep contrast with the same pen.

metadata.name: Organicon, variation II #101
metadata.description:
Generative art by Frederik Vanhoutte, @wblut
One of 128 unique generators creating an endless sequence of iterations with fixed features

Organicon, variation II is a slow piece, meant to build on the screen. A small counter in the lower-right corner displays the progress.

Interface: on first load the piece operates in active mode. In this mode an iteration is cleared 30s after completion and replaced by the next iteration. This mode is indicated by a flashing dot in the upper-right corner.

A first mouse click disables active mode. The current iteration will complete and remain on screen. A second mouse click clears the screen, loads the next iteration, and reenables active mode.

metadata.name: BLOTTER #4
metadata.description:
Generative project that combines the creation of visual elements using artificial intelligence and digital collage.
It contains 101 pngs with transparency distributed in 8 different layers, which enables it to generate more than 222 million possible combinations.

metadata.name: Puxadinho #47
metadata.description:
"Puxadinho" is an expression used in Brazil to refer to the expansion of a house, often without planning, just by "pulling" more built area.

Generally practiced in more peripheral neighborhoods, this annexed construction happens vertically, due to lack of space on the land. 


For this piece I've used p5.js and scribble library

metadata.name: Minimal Scapes #24
metadata.description:
I keep focused and fascinated by minimal compositions and Minimal Scapes is a realization of that exploration as an artist. 

On Minimal Scapes, I recreate several types of hills, mountains, and ground elements on different layers in order to create a sense of depth, also I combine different sky shades and sun sizes, reflecting sunsets & sunrises.

Type of Scapes
Canyon Scape
Mountain Scape
Desert Scape
Ocean Scape

My connection with the earth continues with Minimal Scapes, and it is reflected in the colors that I’ve selected, which very much define which type of scape is minted.

Made with ❤️ & pj5s

By CodeNFT (Clementine Novak)
October 2022
tags: p5 generative art landscape sunset ocean desert

metadata.name: GEN XYZ Das Occult #3591
metadata.description:
A 10k Generative Profile Pic collection
GEN XYZ Das Occult - by culla - @tamccullough

move over cryptopunks
there is a new group on the scene

100% code - not an image composition

A bunch of common palettes
A selection of rare palettes
And a smaller set of ultra rare palettes
However, rarity will be based on what combinations the code produces

The majority of tokens will not have a special trait
However your token might have one or even multiple special traits
But, be aware that only the last special trait added will be listed in the features

Even then, look closely, because not all aspects of the canvas are included in the features. Collectors should still look closely and choose what they like when buying on secondary.

follow culla on twitter for updates. Or maybe __acolyte__

Thank you for supporting an emerging artist in the generative art space

Access List reserves were given to holders of the following PFP collections created by culla
2x for each Basqunk held
1x for each Inkspunk, TwoFourQunk, V0iD, DeeManz, Punkasso and CR0$$KULL
You would have needed to transfer the above tokens to your mint wallet at the time of the snapshot

share your tokens on social media with #genxyznft

metadata.name: Ailerons #93
metadata.description:
Ailerons, littering the factory floor, custom made and ready to be fitted to their respective aircraft. An accent trickles across the canvas, coloring any object in its path.

A study of light, built entirely in a 2d renderer, creating light and shadow with math and logic.

Press 's' to save a .png

Created with p5.js and chroma.js
